
                                            The Energy Department on Monday confirmed that petrol is going up 71 cents per litre.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Automobile Association has warned motorists to expect further fuel hikes in the new year after Monday's announcement of a significant rise. The Energy Department on Monday confirmed that petrol is going up 71 cents per litre. From Wednesday, South Africans will also have to cough up between 57 and 60 cents more for diesel. The AA's Layton Beard said: South Africa’s economic situation, in our opinion, remains weak. And our view is still that further fuel price hikes can be expected going into the first quarter of 2018.” Illuminating paraffin is going up between 70 and 98 cents per litre.